ap_petct_h2_7:"7. Where to Get PET-CT in Hong Kong",
ap_petct_p_13:"Major medical institutions offering PET-CT in Hong Kong include:",
ap_petct_ul6_1:"<strong>CUHK Medical Centre</strong>: Equipped with GE Discovery MI digital PET-CT, located in Sha Tin, price approximately HKD 12,000-18,000",
ap_petct_ul6_2:"<strong>Gleneagles Hong Kong Hospital</strong>: Equipped with Siemens Biograph series PET-CT, located in Wong Chuk Hang, price approximately HKD 11,000-17,000",
ap_petct_ul6_3:"<strong>Hong Kong Sanatorium & Hospital</strong>: Latest GE PET-CT, located in Happy Valley, price approximately HKD 13,000-20,000",
ap_petct_ul6_4:"<strong>Baptist Hospital</strong>: Located in Kowloon Tong, price approximately HKD 10,000-15,000",
ap_petct_ul6_5:"<strong>Union Hospital</strong>: Located in Tai Wai, Sha Tin, price approximately HKD 10,000-16,000",
ap_petct_ul6_6:"<strong>Hong Kong Adventist Hospital</strong>: Both Stubbs Road and Tsuen Wan locations offer PET-CT services",
ap_petct_p_14:"PET-CT costs in Hong Kong range from approximately HKD 10,000 to 18,000, depending on scan coverage (whole-body or localized), contrast use, and whether physician consultation and interpretation are included. Some hospitals include tracer fees and radiologist reading fees in the package, while others charge separately. It is recommended to confirm the final cost breakdown with the hospital at the time of booking.",
ap_petct_h2_8:"Summary",
ap_petct_p_15:"PET-CT is a vital tool in oncology, offering irreplaceable value in cancer staging, treatment response assessment, and recurrence monitoring. Hong Kong's advanced PET-CT equipment, standardized procedures, and experienced medical teams make it an ideal choice for this examination. If you or a family member is facing cancer diagnosis or treatment decisions, we recommend thorough discussion with a specialist to determine whether PET-CT is appropriate and which facility and plan best suit your needs.",
ap_petct_cta_title:"Need to schedule a PET-CT in Hong Kong or want to learn more?",
