ap_cuhk_intro:"CUHK Medical Centre (CUHKMC) is a rising star in Hong Kong's healthcare landscape. Since officially opening in September 2021, this private teaching hospital fully owned by The Chinese University of Hong Kong has rapidly earned widespread recognition for its advanced facilities, digital healthcare system, and patient-centred service philosophy. This article provides a comprehensive introduction to the health check centre at CUHK Medical Centre and its related services.",
ap_cuhk_h2_1:"1. Hospital Background and Positioning",
ap_cuhk_p_1:"Located in Sha Tin, adjacent to the CUHK campus and University MTR Station, CUHKMC enjoys a convenient location. With a total investment of approximately HKD 6.3 billion, the 13-storey hospital has a gross floor area of about 130,000 square metres and 516 beds. As a non-profit private teaching hospital, CUHKMC integrates CUHK's Faculty of Medicine research and clinical resources into daily practice, achieving an 'integrated teaching and research' model.",
ap_cuhk_p_2:"The hospital's mission is to become a benchmark for smart healthcare in Hong Kong. One of its defining features is the comprehensive implementation of a 'paperless' electronic medical record system — a pioneering move among Hong Kong private hospitals. The hospital uses an electronic medical record system (CMS) compatible with the Hospital Authority (HA), enabling smoother transfer of patient records between public hospitals and CUHKMC.",
ap_cuhk_h2_2:"2. Health Check Centre Overview",
ap_cuhk_p_3:"CUHKMC's health check centre (Health Management Centre) is located on the second floor, with a dedicated reception area and examination pathway separate from the outpatient clinic, ensuring privacy and comfort. The centre operates by appointment only, strictly controlling the daily number of patients to guarantee sufficient physician time and service quality.",
ap_cuhk_h3_1:"Equipment and Technology",
ap_cuhk_p_4:"The health check centre is equipped with a range of advanced imaging diagnostic devices:",
ap_cuhk_ul1_1:"<strong>3T MRI</strong>: Siemens Vida 3T MRI with BioMatrix technology that automatically corrects respiratory motion artefacts, delivering industry-leading image quality",
ap_cuhk_ul1_2:"<strong>256-Slice CT</strong>: Siemens SOMATOM Force dual-source CT with radiation doses as low as 20% of traditional CT, completing a cardiac scan in 0.25 seconds — ideal for cardiovascular screening",
ap_cuhk_ul1_3:"<strong>PET-CT</strong>: Siemens Biograph Vision PET-CT with FlowMotion continuous scanning technology for rapid whole-body cancer screening",
ap_cuhk_ul1_4:"<strong>Digital Mammography</strong>: Equipped with tomosynthesis technology for higher sensitivity in dense breast tissue",
ap_cuhk_ul1_5:"<strong>Advanced Ultrasound</strong>: Multiple Siemens ACUSON series ultrasound systems supporting elastography, contrast imaging and other cutting-edge functions",
ap_cuhk_h3_2:"Health Check Packages",
ap_cuhk_p_5:"CUHKMC offers a variety of health check packages to meet different needs:",
ap_cuhk_tbl_1_1:"Package Name",
ap_cuhk_tbl_1_2:"Main Items",
ap_cuhk_tbl_1_3:"Duration",
ap_cuhk_tbl_1_4:"Reference Price",
ap_cuhk_tbl_2_1:"Basic Health Check",
ap_cuhk_tbl_2_2:"Blood routine, liver function, renal function, lipids, glucose, uric acid, urinalysis, physical exam, chest X-ray",
ap_cuhk_tbl_2_3:"~2 hours",
ap_cuhk_tbl_2_4:"HKD 4,500",
