ap_sgcost_tbl_2_11:"VIP Suite",
ap_sgcost_tbl_2_12:"1,500 - 4,000+",
ap_sgcost_p_8:"It is worth noting that ward charges in Singapore typically do not include doctor's round fees, medication costs, or examination fees, which are billed separately.",
ap_sgcost_h3_4:"Total Inpatient Cost Examples",
ap_sgcost_p_9:"Below are reference ranges for total inpatient treatment costs for common conditions (including surgery, bed, medication, examination fees, etc.):",
ap_sgcost_ul2_1:"Coronary Artery Bypass Grafting (CABG): SGD 60,000 - 100,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_2:"Heart Valve Replacement: SGD 50,000 - 90,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_3:"Percutaneous Coronary Intervention (PCI, Stent): SGD 20,000 - 40,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_4:"Total Hip Replacement: SGD 25,000 - 45,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_5:"Total Knee Replacement: SGD 25,000 - 45,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_6:"Laparoscopic Cholecystectomy: SGD 10,000 - 18,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_7:"Colon Cancer Resection: SGD 30,000 - 60,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_8:"Lung Cancer Resection: SGD 35,000 - 65,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_9:"Brain Tumor Resection: SGD 40,000 - 80,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_10:"Cesarean Section: SGD 10,000 - 20,000",
ap_sgcost_ul2_11:"Natural Delivery (including hospital stay): SGD 8,000 - 15,000",
ap_sgcost_h2_4:"IV. Comparison with Hong Kong Medical Costs",
ap_sgcost_p_10:"Hong Kong and Singapore are both top-tier medical centers in Asia, with comparable medical standards and service quality, but there are significant differences in costs. Overall, Singapore's private medical costs are approximately 20-40% higher than Hong Kong's. The specific comparison is as follows:",
